    <h1>Pavatar</h1>
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>This PHP library implements <a href="http://www.pavatar.com/">Pavatar</a>, an open specification for a decentralized way of including avatars (user-defined images, such as photos) in web applications.</p>
    <p>Supporting web applications is easy, through a simple <abbr title="Application Programming Interface">API</abbr> or, better yet, creating plugins.  It currently includes plugins for b2evolution and WordPress.</p>
    <p>The current version is @VERSION@.</p>
    <p><a href="http://github.com/keithbowes/pavatar/">More information</a>.</p>
    <h2>Thanks To</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="http://jeenaparadies.net/">Jeena Paradies</a>, author of the Pavatar spec</li>
      <li><a href="http://sourceforge.net/users/nijineko">James Nicholls</a>, creator of the default Pavatar icon</li>
    </ul>
  </body>
